other_tests.findings: The liver is diffusely echogenic with a smooth contour. A complex cyst in segment V (superficial cyst measures up to 1.5 cm and a deeper cyst measures up to 2.6 cm). The gallbladder is moderately distended with moderate wall edema and pericholecystic fluid, containing a large gallstone and possibly adherent sludge or a large gallbladder polyp (area approximately 2.3 x 1.4 cm). No intrahepatic biliary dilation and no ascites.
